Argo CD Installation Steps
Argo CD is a declarative continuous delivery tool for Kubernetes. It can be used as a standalone tool or as part of your CI/CD workflow to deliver needed resources to your clusters.

‚úÖ Installation Process:
bash
Copy
Edit
# Create a namespace for Argo CD
kubectl create namespace argocd

# Install Argo CD using the official manifest
kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj/argo-cd/stable/manifests/install.yaml

# Get pods in argocd namespace
kubectl get pods -n argocd

# Get services in argocd namespace
kubectl get svc -n argocd

# Edit the argocd-server service to expose it (optional)
kubectl edit svc argocd-server -n argocd

# Alternatively, get all services to find the NodePort
kubectl get svc -n argocd
üåê Accessing the Argo CD UI:
bash
Copy
Edit
# Get NodePort of the server (check type NodePort or use port-forward)
kubectl get svc -n argocd

# Get the secret (for retrieving initial admin password)
kubectl get secrets -n argocd
üîê Retrieve Admin Credentials:
bash
Copy
Edit
# Extract the initial admin password
kubectl edit secret argocd-initial-admin-secret -n argocd
Default username: admin

The password will be encoded in base64; decode it using:

bash
Copy
Edit
echo <base64-password> | base64 -d
